eavily. B has more. So C may be more balanced despite lacking weather skill. However weather assessment is important for long-distance. But we cannot assume remedy. The lack of weather skill is a technical gap. However C has excellent attention and quick decisions, which may help. But weather assessment is a specific skill.\n\nWe need to decide. The group currently has two votes for C, one for B. As agent_2, we can reconsider. The instruction says we should update position if combined evidence supports a different candidate. The combined evidence now shows that B's cooperation issues are significant. C's positives include reliability and positive atmosphere. The technical gap (weather) is notable but maybe less than cooperation deficits. The instruction says \"A candidate with balanced evidence across the essential criteria may be better than a candidate with one very strong trait but repeated cooperation drawbacks.\" B has strong technical but repeated cooperation drawbacks. C has balanced but missing weather. So likely C is better.\n\nThus I will change vote to Candidate C, with moderate confidence.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE with reasoning summary, referencing evidence from others (Agent 1 and Agent 3). Also note my earlier position B.\n\nNow output."}
